imdb.plot outline: Bornebusch i tevefabriken - or The TV Factory - is a show about TV-series hosted by the Swedish actress and script writer Josephine Bornebusch, produced by SVT/Sveriges Television, the largest public service TV company in Scandinavia. The first season premiered in March 2016. The show visited sets like The Bridge in Sweden/Denmark, Downton Abbey in Great Britain and Orange is the New Black in the US, and included in-depth interviews with actors like Titus Welliver, Anthony Andrews, Yael Stone, Frances Conroy and tv-creators like Tim van Patten, Michelle MacLaren and Johan Renck. The mission of Bornebusch i tevefabriken is to dig into the beautiful, exciting and still expanding universe of TV-series; to get behind the scenes, to meet the creators and try to find out how and why TV-series became the most vitalised and exciting place for modern drama and comedy on screen today.
imdb.title: Bornebusch i tevefabriken
plot: A documentary series from SVT/Swedish Television - the biggest broadcasting public service company in Scandinavia - that digs into the new golden age of TV-shows.

The mission of _Bornebusch i tevefabriken_ (qv) is to dig into the beautiful, exciting and still expanding universe of TV-series; to get behind the scenes, to meet the creators and try to find out how and why TV-series became the most vitalised and exciting place for modern drama and comedy on screen today.
